  "prompt": "Why do people ask questions on Quora but do nothing?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why people ask questions on Quora without taking action:\n\n1. Curiosity\n- Simply wanting to know information\n- Seeking different perspectives\n- Exploring a topic without immediate intention to act\n\n2. Psychological factors\n- Procrastination\n- Lack of motivation\n- Fear of failure\n- Comfort in theoretical knowledge\n\n3. Information gathering\n- Collecting insights\n- Comparing different viewpoints\n- Researching before making a decision\n\n4. Limited commitment\n- No real intention to implement\n- Passive engagement\n- Enjoying intellectual discussion\n\n5. Seeking validation\n- Wanting to understand if their thoughts are reasonable\n- Looking for confirmation or alternative viewpoints\n\n6. Time and effort constraints\n- Finding it easier to ask than to execute\n- Perceived complexity of implementation\n- Feeling overwhelmed by potential steps\n\n7. Online behavior\n- Enjoying passive participation\n- Low-stakes interaction\n- Easy accessibility of platforms like Quora\n\n8. Analysis paralysis\n- Too many options\n- Difficulty in deciding next steps\n- Overthinking potential outcomes\n\nWhile asking questions is valuable for learning, translating knowledge into action requires additional motivation, planning, and commitment.",
